INGREDIENTS

50g butter
1 leek, sliced
1,25l fish stock 
450g potatoes, cubed
1 carrot, sliced
450g salmon fillet cut into small chunks
250ml cream
10g fresh dill, finely chopped
salt and pepper


INSTRUCTIONS
 
Melt the butter. 
Add the sliced leek and saute about 7 minutes.
Add the stock, carrot and potatoes. 
Bring to a boil and cook for about 10 minutes over medium heat. 
Add the salmon chunks and the cream, and cook until it starts to boil.
Turn off the heat and add the dill, salt and pepper. 
Close the lid and wait for another 10 minutes. Enjoy!
